        <Description2><![CDATA[The EposService module manages the connection and provides information to the "EPOS via Internet" backend. It communicates if the mower wants correction/assist data and provides a way for the backend to communicate its status to the mower.

##### What does "available" mean on this family?
The available flag indicates if this mower supports Epos as a service, i.e. is capable of receiving correction data from backend service. It does not reflect whether this mower has an active subscription, that is unknown to the mower.

##### What does "enabled" mean?
Enabled means that the user has selected to use Epos as a service. If EposService is both available and enabled, the mower will expect to receive correction data when needed.
]]></Description2>
